Appendix A
ALTERNATIVE B Plantation and Road Management with No Timber Harvest Restore plantations and roads and let nature do the rest
GOAL 1:
Protect and enhance late-successional and oldgrowth forest ecosystems.
On decommissioned and BLM-controlled roads, control noxious weeds within 10 years sufficient to ensure they do not penetrate into latesuccessional stands.
Inventory roads within or adjacent to late-successional stands for the presence of noxious weeds.
Remove noxious weeds from BLM-controlled roads, including roads to be decommissioned.
Plant trees or other native species in the decommissioned roads to prevent noxious weeds from becoming established in areas where weed seed is likely to spread into the decommissioned roads.
